# Research: the Honest Spoken Record for Judging

## Step

session.history loses interrupted/list turns (receipt: "The six that need
you:" saved with no list; caller audibly heard it). The judge must score what
was actually SAID. Investigate livekit-agents 1.4.x: transcription/spoken-sync
events, per-segment callbacks, whether interrupted content is truncated or
dropped, and whether our Convex turn rows / transcriptLine field can carry the
true record. Deliverable: an asset stating the recommended capture mechanism
with API receipts, sized for the judge build to consume.

## Result (2026-07-13)

Use LiveKit's public `conversation_item_added` event and persist every committed
user/assistant message as an append-only spoken item. In installed
livekit-agents 1.4.2, interrupted assistant output is replaced with the
synchronized transcript from completed playout before the message is committed;
the event therefore carries the package's best record of what reached the
caller, including `item.interrupted`.

The current Convex `addTurn.transcriptLine` path is not sufficient: no handler
sends it, Convex keeps it only in the session's rolling 12-line tail, and the
inserted turn row drops it. Add a dedicated spoken-item mutation/table with
room, sequence, message ID, speaker, text, interruption flag, and commit time.

The stated receipt did not reproduce: the file currently at
`~/.joelclaw/workspace/memory/voice/2026-07-12-151052.md:33-42` contains the
heading and all six list items. That weakens the specific claim that history
dropped this turn, but not the recommendation to capture committed items live.

Full mechanism, source line receipts, schema contract, and canary:
[Spoken record capture](./spoken-record-capture.svx).
